caption: AWESOME!!!

I was craving sushi and ordered here from Doordash ... here is day 2 and I just placed another order lol me and my daughter loves the “ Dynamite Roll “ and the General Tos’ wings. I will have to explore the menu so far loving everything.
Have had great takeout from here! Would recommend the Thai Basil fried rice-delicious! Looking forward to ordering takeout again soon.

This restaurant is obviously one of the tastiest place in the region. Every time I come to this place I am profoundly glad. They manage their very high  level service and the topmost level of food  they give. You will be always satisfied with this restaurant. Very  recommended.
I simply love their dishes. I always get good customer service here. The place is well kept and the employees are always welcoming. Keep up the good work.
Dynamite Roll is good... service and customer service needs alot of work
Person who took my order was rude, and food was sub par
Lets just say i have been back twice in a week. Food is excellent!'Long wait in line because its that good so call ahead. I order combo rice and egg foo young. Best in the city
Slow Service
Main place in downtown Silver Spring for affordable and delicious sushi take-out.

This place is certainly one of the coolest place in the region. Anytime I go there I am deeply satisfied. They keep their high  level service and the highest level of cooking  they offer. You can never go wrong with this place. Very  recommended.

I like city taste, it’s affordable and there’s a lot of variety. I use to go here all the time before I went plant based. The spicy crab roll and spicy tuna were always my go-to budget roll. Not if you eat sushi a lot, it might not be the best place you have ever been do but for the price you can’t beat it!
Omg the best I’ve had since being in silver springs MD
Very good food 👍👍👍
Best takeout in silver spring ! Thai /Chinese/sushi by far . Super friendly and they have great prices . There lunch specials are good as well.
Good value, good taste, good service for take away. I'm happy.
Good customer Service
The food is so good and the owners are nice people .
The spot is wonderful and roomy, the food was delicious and the prices were very affordable. rapidly, effective service and very personal waiters. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
This restaurant is nice and roomy, the menu was delightful and the rates were very reasonable. quickly, productive service and very personal waiters. Highly recommended.
First time. I liked it.
Best Chinese food in Silver Spring, hands down. The food is delicious and authentic, and the prices are very reasonable. Overall a great place to eat.

I celebrated my nomination today in this fine place. Well we passed a terrific evening and the venue was no doubt the reason for the strong event. The crew  contributed in a pleasant way, the food was appetizing and my buddies were extremely  pleased. We shall absolutely come back again for more celebrations. thanks very much.
EXCELLENT taste n presentation of great food..love.it
(Translated by Google) Delicious food.  (Original) Deliciosa comida.
Food was delicious and they gave us the lunch special price even though we came in a few minutes after it was over
Great Menu, Great Taste, Courteous Service, Short Wait Time...
This place has first-rate service as well as enjoyable food. One of my favourite restaurants around town. The food arrived fast and the prices were fair. Recommended.

we ordered carry out for the 1 st time  last night.  The food arrived in less than the alloted time ,which was impressive given it was a Friday night.The dishes were  good .Dinners:Deluxe Sushi Dinner, Hibachi Combo Set Course and Kung Pao, Jumbo Shrimp. Appetizers were: Spring rolls,Hot and Sour Soup and Miso soup.Problem was  two fold; 1 st we got (2) orders of Miso soup and no Hot and Sour. 2nd; The miso soup was  not good. We didnt want to eat more than a small amount of either containers.  Maybe it was a bad batch but I would not recommend ordering  Miso Soup to anyone.

I like their food. It's light on the grease and salt. Their sushi is really good too. No parking on the street except for weekends and even then it's hard to find a spot. Weekends and if you enter after 7pm, it's free to park across the street. Other times, it's free to park for 15 mins.
Food and service very good.
The Best Sushi!!

Good food but do not order to be delivered.  We did it once and waited hours (pretty much until they closed) to get our food. They are 0.3 miles from where we live, if we knew we would have picked up our order.
We love this place and go here all the time. The food is always fresh and delicious.
Great
If you really like sushi do not have any expectation. But if you looking a quick fix go ahead.
Very fast service, excellent prices (especially for lunch special). To go may be best as seating is very limited.

(Translated by Google) Good place on weekdays for those who want to order take-out. Or have lunch there. I mean lunches ... include a soda for less than $ 10. Chinese Food. Good taste.  (Original) Buen lugar en dias de semana para quienes quieran ordenar para llevar. O almorzar alli mismo. Me refiero a los almuerzos... incluyen una soda por menos de $10. Comida china. Buen sabor.
Horrid food, I'm sorry but if you think this is quality food then your palate is very limited and sad.

Good food but definately pricey. If you are getting food for delivery, make sure you tell them to not bring signature copy receipt. I order from them ALL the time. I always tip them & they are only located a couple blocks away from my house. I ordered today & spent about 40$ so I decided not to tip. I signed the receipt copy & handed him back the receipt. He looked at the paper then looked at me and said "and the tip?" I found that really rude that he demanded a tip so I told him no tip today. He gave me an ugly look as he walk away. DEFINATELY NEVER EATING THERE AGAIN. CUSTOMER SERVICE WAS TERRIBLE!!!

Ok y'all this is my Friday night treat! I always order the Kung Pao Shrimp with an order (or 2) of sushi from their 35% off menu (don't judge me). Their food is always fresh and flavorful! Sushi is made fresh by their sushi chefs while you watch! They are always nice and their restaurant is small and very clean! One thing...if you want to pick up logistics are a bit tight because you will not be able to park and run in, as it is on a busy street with no parking. There is a parking garage directly across the street. If I order to go, I will just park across the street. If I order pick up, I usually have to take my daughter with me so she can run in and I circle the block. If you stand on the street you will get a ticket. It is a heavy pedestrian area so watch out for that as well.
Amazing food for a modest price. My favorite lunch place!

We had Combination lo mein and General Tso’s Chicken, Beef and Broccoli. All of it was Delicious. Very good quality food. The place is small but give this place a try if your looking for good Chinese food.

Absolutely no care given too our order being late. They did not even care that they did not even expect our order to be delivered. The did not even expect us to receive a receive a refund. Then upcharged us $10 to cancel our order. They are a rip off. Do not order from this place. I have never given 1 star before.
I love this place, food taste good, price are incredibles and the service is good. Highly recommended
Great service and hospitality

I buy sushi from City Taste at least once a week. The lunch special comes with a salad or miso soup. A few weeks ago I found a bug in my salad. When I went back and showed it to them, they said it wasn't a bug. Always check your food before you eat it here, you never know what you'll find or if your order will be correct.
Excellent food! Great prices and very large portions. Sushi is very fresh and super tasty! Staff is friendly and welcoming. We will make this a regular stop every time we are in town.

Perfect Price for perfectly amazing food. There is always the right amount of what you pay for with anything you order and everything taste great. The sushi is beautifully exhibited and also taste amazing as well. Would highly recommend for anyone seeking our great tasting chinese.

The food was fine. We ordered a dumplings which were delicious. Both my friend and I got meals that came with soup however we were not able to choose the type of soup. I had the hibachi chicken and shrimp and my friend got the chicken katsu. Both were fine but the Katsu was served like an appetizer that came with rice and soup. It came with like 4 full chicken breasts of katsu style chicken. It was definitely too much for a meal for one person. I’ve had Katsu in Japan and this did not taste authentic. The service was fine but overall was not impressed with my experience. I probably won’t I’ll not be returning to this restaurant.

Ordered food today. Shrump wiyh mixed vegatsbles and triple delight. Horrible. I brought food from yhis place before and it was very good BUT toda Saturdsy, July 6tyh at 4pm it was not edible. Not sure who was Cooking BUT  (THEY SHOULD NOT COOK). CAN'T GO BACK.

My boyfriend and I we're craving (non-authentic) Chinese food (although they probably have more authentic options too), and there orange chicken and general tsos really hit the spot!  The portion size was perfect (enough for me when I'm really hungry, but often sually enough for two meals).  Well cooked food and fast and friendly service!
Everyone was very nice. The food was just okay. The reviews made me think that food was going to wow me. That didn't happen. 😔

It's great sushi and very welcoming service. Love this place! They offer sit in dining or carryout. There's a convenient parking garage across from the location. My favorite is anything tempura, they have a nice variety. Also super affordable! Definitely worth it if you like sushi, and they do offer other Asian Cuisines as well. Highly recommend this place.
Always fresh, always delicious! I typically order the General Tso Chicken, extra crispy and spicy but this time I went for the Crispy Beef and it did not disappoint!
Best Chinese food in Silver Spring. The sushi is pretty good too!
Nice food and service you can eat in or take out.

We ordered a lot of food, and they do have a variety of options to choose from. The appitizers came after the main entrée which was a bummer, but the sushi was really good. The chef special sushis are must try! We reordered some more sushi and a dessert, but like before, the dessert came before the food! Would recommend the place for good food, but service, maybe..
Have ordered Chinese, Sushi, and Thai from here. Food is pretty solid. Delivery times vary considerably during peak times.

I was pleasantly surprised by how good it is!, now, as it's almost always the case with restaurant food, it's a little salty, obviously they do this to enhance flavors. They have a great lunch special under $8, and next time I'm having sashimi. On the downside,  one of the servers is very mean, and this changes the equation,  now I'm not so sure I'm ever coming back. Sad!
I love my mixed fries rice with beef chicken and the shrimp.the shrimp was tasty fresh and delicious and the service was fast
Great food

The food is delicious.  I've been to this restaurant twice and both times they've messed up our payment.  If you go here and pay by credit card, make sure to double check your credit card statement.  We will not be returning.
Good sushi
Great food at affordable price. Very friendly staff. Ordered pick-up, got a free sushi.

We were really pleased by a delivery order we had, so when we were looking for a place to eat while we were out, we thought to give it a try. The food is good, but I think we'll stick to delivery. The dining room is small, and it was nearly impossible to manage with small children. I even thought our food wasn't as good as when we had ordered out! I'm eager to give them another chance, though. But next time, delivery again.
Good restaruant. Convient and fast. Recommended.
Cheap quality, bad food. Didn't finish it. Food was ready in 2 min. They didn't cook it.waa probably sitting there.
I just picked up my delivery of sushi for the first time there and I was pleasantly satisfied with my order and the quality of the dishes. I had ample amounts of ginger & wasabi.
Best tasting and value on Chinese and Japanese food.
We visit at least 1x a month for Dinner.  Good sushi and Thai. Great price point on Sushi.

City Taste is an awesome option for Asian cuisine in DTSS. The menu is varied and covers Thai, Chinese, and Japanese dishes. The lunch specials are generous and delicious, with many of the dishes costing $10 or less and include 1-2 sides. I opted for the 3 roll sushi lunch special, and the rolls were beautiful and delicious.  I was thrilled to find Dan Dan Noodles on the menu, but I was wearing a white blouse so that wasn't an option for lunch. Fear not, I still ordered it to-go to enjoy later, and I appreciate that CT took the time to package the broth and noodles separately. This spot is relatively new and undiscovered compared to the other sushi in the area, so I'd definitely give it a try when the craving hits.
Very nice ambiance good variety and attention to guest  5 star out of 5
Good service, great food!
Spend our friends anniversary here.  Calm and relaxing atmosphere with good service.  Food was great.
Best price for quality sushi, good service too
Excellent place! Great prices and the food is amazing especially the fried rice and sushi!
Love the food here! Varied menu with very tasty vegan choices. All the food served tastefully.
It always has great and friendly staff, and the food is always great! I wish I could eat there everyday.
We eat lunch here a lot the food and service is consistently good.
Very good sushi!!!
Great menu, service is calm and friendly. Very pleased with quality of food.
Excellent Thai food, and sushi selections
Good food but bad customer service
The chicken was very chewy.
Best Chinese and sushi delivery in the area and AMAZING value. It’s been our family’s go to for delivery since it opened and it never disappoints.
Staff is always friendly and nice, and food is always correct, and hot! Always a regular!

Good food. The food comes out fast (and freshly prepared), the prices are good, and the food is delicious. Ordered a general Tsao's Chicken and it was some of the best chicken I've ever had - it was hot and crispy (not soggy stuff you'd get from Panda Express), sweet but NOT too sweet (I dislike extremely sweet foods), and had a nice amount of spice to it to give it a little kick (they add in garlic and peppers). Absolutely delicious. However, some of their other dishes are too sweet (eg. garlic sauce dishes) and have little taste due to lack of spices.

went here with a group so I not only got to see the diversity of the menu in words but on the table. the specials are great and even the entrees are super competitive with the specials prices. so many options between sushi or Chinese dishes... all the options of both a sushi and Chinese restaurant. I ordered my favorite Chinese dish and it was exactly how I like it. others ordered sushi and loved it and it looked great. the portions are great and many dishes come with a spring roll which you may not have room for if you get one of their soups to start. the atmosphere is cozy with not much seating. while we were there so many people came in to get carry out so it must be a local favorite. my only complaint is that water glasses should be refilled more often.

The only reason I am writing this review is because the business asked why I gave one star. Some of the fish on the sushi plate I ordered was bad and I got sick because I ate some of them before I realized. The tempura prawns were EXTREMELY oily (yes I know they are fried but the sheet of paper under them was soaked by the time they brought it out to the table). Service was very slow even though there were only 2 other tables occupied, they had already been served. The other dish we ordered was more celery and oil than meat. Tea was luke warm, not hot at all. For all of those issues I gave one star.
Friendly service.  Good food.
Good food!

Finally!!  Silver Spring has excellent Chinese food!  We ordered our regular favorites - General Tso’s chicken, crispy beef, double cooked pork, and Kung Pao chicken. Each dish was outstanding. And they have beer!  Don’t miss this place.
Really like this place.  Don't know why I keep getting asked to rate it from this Google maps app

Service was great! They were really nice and attentive. I ordered a chicken with brócoli - the chicken was just a bit bland (needed a bit salt). But my boyfriend ordered the general tso chicken, and it was so good! We even got the sushi tempura and that was delicious as well. Definitely worth to try.
Good taste, friendly staff and decent price.sure it is a bit americanized flavor, but absolutely worth every penny spent.

AWFUL!!  TERRIBLE!! This place ripped me off. The food was bland at best and the customer service very poor. I ordered takeout, a dish that was served with shrimp, it was not what I expected so I went back to request shrimp and broccoli. Much to my dismay, my new ordered was prepared with the shrimp from the “returned “ order. What a huge waste of money!! The shrimp were so mushy and over cooked since they had already been prepared once. What a rip off!
The food and service is great here. Nice people
Always delicious!  Friendly staff!
Everything is made with quality and care
This is my favorite chinese food restaurant in Silver Spring there food is good for multiple dishes that I have tried. There lunch menu specials have a lot of variety.

My sister and I went here for the first time on a Wednesday afternoon. The food was very very good and with just enough spice. I had the Shrimp and Scallops with Garlic sauce and she had the Mao Pao Tofu. As you can see in the pictures that food looked great and trust me tasted even better. We highly recommend. They also have a special on sushi rolls that are up to 35% off and very good price for their lunch offers.

Received the menu in the mail and was happy to see a new Chinese place in the area that actually had decent prices... I was so happy when we received the food at it was actually 1) delivered quickly (within 30 mins of calling!) 2) the order was correct 3) the food was all Very good!! Finally a Chinese place in Silver Spring that is Very Good and has reasonable prices. We got: steamed dumplings, kung pao Chicken, teriyaki chicken (included miso soup), and jedi roll. They threw in a California Roll for free with the order over $30... All that for $35 (plus driver tip)!!  Can't wait to order from City Taste again!
Delicious Pan-Asian cuisine. It's my first time eating here and now I can't really find any reason to go anywhere else. Best crispy beef I've had in years!
Delicious pad Thai and veggies!!

My new favorite sushi spot! The price is right and the fish was fresh. I had the dynamite roll, volcano roll and the fire & ice roll for $18. They were are all great. The rolls come in either 4, 6, or 8 depending on which rolls you get. I will definitely be going back.
Was good but not great..barest minimal curry selection
Delicious food.
Great house noodle soup, clean restaurant and polite courteous service..
Good food
Kung Paso chicken and shrimp was very tasty. Service was prompt and simple.
Excellent food and service
Ok
So good. Sushi is amazing! Staff is amazing! Atmosphere is amazing!

First time by I picked up take out.  The place is a bit tucked away -- I was not sure what to expect.  The staff were very friendly and enthusiastic.  The place seemed neat and clean with a few tables with views of the Silver Spring hustle and bustle.  What I took away was good food, well put together, packaged neatly, and pretty tasty to boot.  I look forward to trying a broader range of dishes!
Good, fresh sushi at an affordable price. And they do take out!
Great Chinese and other Asian style food. Some favorite standard dishes and several dishes you don't see everywhere else. The food is very freshly prepared and not greasy. The service is excellent.

The food is good. I've tried several things. I recommend the Kung pao. The service is still learning their role. I've had a few orders messed up, but they fix it quickly and without complaint. Remember, the place is pretty new. The place is clean and the prices are good. Try it out!
The price is right! Also, surprisingly good Dan Dan Noodles!

Delicious food that affordable, and comes out very fast too! The food is way better than any other regular Chinese restaurant. The drunken noodles, General Tsao's Chicken are delicious. I definitely would recommend and I would eat here again Myself. They have a nice clean and spacious dining area. The bathroom is clean too.

We ate here for the first time this evening, and I recommend this restaurant to everyone wanting great food, great atmosphere and exceptional service. Hopefully you’ll get to meet Ms. Lin, she is very kind and interesting.
This is a nice small sit down chinese/thai/sushi restaurant. The staff are very kind. They made a mistake on my takeout order but upon calling, they quickly rectified the situation.
Best Kung Pao Chicken I have ever had...

Fans of the former Asian Bistro should rejoice!  City Taste is pretty similar and some of the dishes have even been better.  I have tried the general tso's chicken and kung pao chicken.  Both times I asked for it very spicy and was not disappointed.  Soup can be added to the lunch specials for only $1 which is a great deal.  There are also sushi and hibachi lunch combos.

Ordered a Thai basil fried rice and vegi tempura. This is my first time writing a review for any restaurant. I really wanted this place to be good but very disappointed. I asked for the friend rice to be spicy and obviously it wasn't. The food was bland, no salt or flavor. The main dish came first and I had to waite a while before getting the appetizer. It's a new place hope they can improve.
They Deliver!!! That's an automatic 5 stars lol!!! The lady who took my order was really sweet and my food was tasty and delivery time was fairly quick 😊

The food is AMAZING, the service is fast and friendly, and the setting is pleasant. A dinner serving is a solid dinner, with a little left to reheat the next day for lunch. The food still tastes great when reheated, even several days later. I won't be going anywhere else for Chinese.

Absolutely impressed on all levels and in all categories at this new sushi spot in downtown SS. Food is simply amazing. Presentation is top notch. Will be back for many many lunches and dinners to come. A+++
love the food they made😋😋😋，yummy
Good fresh food. Try the veggie dumplings. The dough is cooked just right. SINGAPORE noodles rocked! Great service.
Extremely tasty food, soothing atmosphere, courteous staff and great prices. Instant favorite. Wonderful establish, I will definitely return.
